Rightwing extremists chase Turkish group, injure five 
Forty young far-rightwingers armed with knives and sticks chased a
group of Turks through the eastern German town of Magdeburg Thursday,
injuring five of them, police said.
The group came across the Turkish people at the end of the afternoon
and chased them through the centre of the town.
Police, who said they made 15 arrests, did not detail the condition of
any of the five injured.
